  "clinical_narrative": "An 81-year-old female underwent pre-procedure coronary angiography revealing 80% stenosis in the left circumflex artery, leading to a planned PTCA. The procedure was performed via right radial artery, involving pre-dilatation, stenting with a single drug-eluting stent (LCX-GRACE 2.75 X 36 mm), and post-dilatation. Final result was excellent with TIMI-III flow and 0% residual stenosis. Post-procedure instructions included long-term dual antiplatelets.",
